Welcome to the Evolute Seller Account Manager

Within the console you have full control over every aspect of your account. Instructions are within each section of this website. You can also find additional information in our User Guide or by contacting our Support Team by clicking help.

Run Reports

Run real time daily trend or period reports on leads you sent to the Evolute marketplace.

Lead Channels must be opened to submit leads to the marketplace. View and edit all your lead channels at any time.

My Settings

Server Post Date & Time

If you are using a Server Post delivery execution you must set the time zone and date format of the CAPTURE_TIME attribute. This will ensure that your system and the Evolute system accurately denote the CAPTURE_TIME for leads.

NOTE: Incorrect CAPTURE_TIME will result in invalid leads.

Product Field Specifications
–
Lists the name-value pairs on each product required for lead submission, including form requirements and validation rules. Provides an example post string for each product to assist in your form post and server post integration.
Schedule

Finance

Payment Summary
–
Allows you to view individual lead transactions and adjustments for each payment based on the day payment was issued.
Schedule

Lead Export

Lead Data Export
–
Displays the attributes for each individual lead you submit, except for contact information.
Schedule

Performance

Daily Lead Limit in last 30 days
–
Provides a one month summary of the number of leads you have sold compared to your lead channel lead limits.
Schedule
Today's Activity Summary
–
Offers a real-time summary of the data leads you have submitted today and your earnings from those sales.
Schedule
Data Lead Activity Summary
–
Shows revenue generated through the Evolute Marketplace by lead channel, tracking values, data range and product.
Schedule
Voice Lead Activity Summary
–
Shows revenue generated through phone calls sent to the Evolute Marketplace by lead channel, toll-free number, date range and product.
Schedule
Lead Quality Summary
–
Shows the performance of recent leads submitted to Evolute based on LeadClass quality scoring.

Your Private Auction Settings

Use the "Price Minimum" settings to specify the minimum price you will accept for Orders from your connected Buyers. Input the amount per lead in the fields below. Buyer Orders with prices equal to or above these amounts will be automatically accepted by your account. Prices entered must be higher than LeadPoint minimums noted under each field

Use the "Required Notice to Change or Cancel" settings to specify the minimum Notice Period that you will accept for an Order. For example, a 3-day Notice Period means that the Buyer must notify you three days in advance of canceling or changing an Order.

The "Default" notice period enables you to set the default selection for Notice Period for a Buyer creating an Order for your leads.
